metadata.title: Piper PA-28 Cherokee
aws::graph::propositions: Brazilian, Argentinian and Chilean Production of Piper PA-28 Cherokee
Piper PA-28 Cherokee aircraft were built under license in Brazil as the Embraer EMB-711A.
Piper PA-28 Cherokee aircraft were built under license in Brazil as the Embraer EMB-711C Corisco.
The Embraer EMB-711C Corisco is equivalent to the Piper PA-28R-200.
Piper PA-28 Cherokee aircraft were built under license in Brazil as the Embraer EMB-711B.
The Embraer EMB-711B is equivalent to the Piper PA-28R-201.
Piper PA-28 Cherokee aircraft were built under license in Brazil as the Embraer EMB-711T.
The Embraer EMB-711T is equivalent to the Piper PA-28RT-201.
Piper PA-28 Cherokee aircraft were built under license in Brazil as the Embraer EMB-711ST Corisco Turbo.
The Embraer EMB-711ST Corisco Turbo is equivalent to the Piper PA-28RT-201T.
Piper PA-28 Cherokee aircraft were built under license in Brazil as the Embraer EMB-712 Tupi.
The Embraer EMB-712 Tupi is equivalent to the Piper PA-28-181.
Piper PA-28 Cherokee aircraft were built under license in Argentina by Chincul SACAIFI.
Chincul SACAIFI is located in San Juan, Argentina.
Chincul SACAIFI built 960 airplanes between 1972 and 1995.
Chincul SACAIFI built the Cherokee Archer.
Chincul SACAIFI built the Dakota.
Chincul SACAIFI built the Arrow.
Chincul SACAIFI built the Turbo Arrow.
The Piper PA-28-236 Dakota was assembled under license by the Maintenance Wing of the Chilean Air Force.
The Maintenance Wing of the Chilean Air Force later became known as ENAER.
By September 1982, 20 Dakotas had been assembled in Chile.

text:
### Brazilian, Argentinian and Chilean production
PA-28s were built under license in Brazil as the Embraer EMB-711A and EMB-711C Corisco (PA-28R-200), EMB-711B (PA-28R-201), EMB-711T (PA-28RT-201) and EMB-711ST Corisco Turbo (PA-28RT-201T) and the EMB-712 Tupi (PA-28-181). Argentinian production was carried out by Chincul SACAIFI of San Juan, Argentina. Chincul S. A. built 960 airplanes between 1972 and 1995, including the Cherokee Archer, Dakota, Arrow and Turbo Arrow. The PA-28-236 Dakota was also assembled under license by the Maintenance Wing of the Chilean Air Force (which later became known as ENAER). By September 1982, 20 Dakotas had been assembled in Chile.
